❌ Problem

AttributeError: 'QGraphicsScene' object has no attribute 'addRoundedRect'

🧠 Why this happens

QGraphicsScene does NOT have addRoundedRect() in PyQt5.

It exists in some Qt C++ contexts, but not exposed the way we tried to use it.

⸻

✅ Fix (simple + correct)

Replace this line:

box = self.scene.addRoundedRect(

with:

rect = QtCore.QRectF(x, y, width, height)
path = QtGui.QPainterPath()
path.addRoundedRect(rect, 8, 8)
box = self.scene.addPath(
    path,
    QtGui.QPen(QtGui.QColor("#3a7aa8"), 1),
    QtGui.QBrush(QtGui.QColor("#112334"))
)

⸻

🔧 Full corrected add_node function

Replace your entire function with this:

def add_node(self, text, x, y):
    width = 210
    height = 44
    rect = QtCore.QRectF(x, y, width, height)
    path = QtGui.QPainterPath()
    path.addRoundedRect(rect, 8, 8)
    box = self.scene.addPath(
        path,
        QtGui.QPen(QtGui.QColor("#3a7aa8"), 1),
        QtGui.QBrush(QtGui.QColor("#112334"))
    )
    label = self.scene.addText(str(text))
    label.setDefaultTextColor(QtGui.QColor("#edf6ff"))
    text_rect = label.boundingRect()
    label.setPos(
        x + (width - text_rect.width()) / 2,
        y + (height - text_rect.height()) / 2
    )
    return box

